### Implementation

### Changes Made

- `src/burnt/core/exceptions.py` - Added `CostBudgetExceeded` exception with `estimate`, `budget_usd`, `label`, and `currency` attributes
- `src/burnt/core/models.py` - Implemented `raise_if_exceeds(budget, label, currency)` method in `CostEstimate` class that:
  - Returns `self` if under budget (chainable)
  - Raises `CostBudgetExceeded` if over budget
  - Warns and returns self if cost is None
  - Uses default currency when not specified
  - Converts currency using Frankfurter API when needed
- `src/burnt/__init__.py` - Exported `CostBudgetExceeded`, added `set_default_currency()` and `get_default_currency()` functions

### Implementation Notes

- Used Frankfurter API for currency conversion to support EUR and other currencies
- Default currency starts at USD for backward compatibility
- Currency parameter is optional - uses default when not specified

